                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#132rc">Fol. 132rc</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 132rc: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘሹም፡ አጋሜ፡ ካሳ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለመድኃኔ፡ ዓለም፡ አድግራት፡ ወስመ፡ ጥምቀቱ፡ ወልደ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሀ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ወበቃለ፡ መምሕርነ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 132rc: This is a book of šum ʾAgame Kasa whose baptismal name is Wäldä ʾArägawi, who has donated it to the (church of) Mädḫane ʿAläm ʾAddǝgrat so that it might be for him a guide to the Kingdom of Heaven. He who stole it or erased (its text) shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul and by the word of our mämhǝr Kidanä Maryam.</q>
                           he note is written in the main hand. Šum ʾAgame Kasa (a son of ras Sǝbḥat) is also mentioned in Additiones to Mss. AMM-008, AMQ-011, BGY-006, MKL-005, MKL-006. He was governor of ʾAgame in 1914-18, 1941-48. Cp. HAGOS GEBRE YOHANNES, “Political History of Tigray: Rivalry for power (1910-1935)”, PhD thesis, Addis Abäba University, 2003, 46.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work, ቅዳሤ፡, has been crudely inscribed in green ink on the front cover.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-signs, in the shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where the omissions written in the margins, in the main hand, belong: fols. 3vb l.2, 4rc l.15, 8rb l.9, 13va l.11, 41rc l.15, 42va l.19, 66ra l.4, 70rc l.12, 84vc l.2, 86va l.16, 95vc l.1, 102ra l.12, 104vb l.20, 105vc l.12, 112ra l.2, 114vc l.15, 117va l.13, 119va l.10, 126ra l.12.&#xD;
- Omitted words and passages are written in interlineally or in the margins, in the main and in a secondary hands: fols. 15vc, 30rc, 53r, 108r, 109vb, 110vc, 114ra, 128v, 131r. &#xD;
- Crude recent notes indicating liturgical occasions upon which the respective Anaphoras are to be celebrated: fols. 90r, 107r, 119v (in the upper margin).&#xD;
- Crude notes, partly in red and pink ink: fols. 99r, 109r, 111r, 116v, 122v, 123r, 124v (in the upper margin).&#xD;
- Fol. 124v (in the left-hand margin): Crude notes.</item>
                     </list>
